title: For Sale:  1866 Springfield Trapdoor
postcontent: This is a fully functioning Model 1866 Springfield Trapdoor Rifle. Marked "FOX STUDIOS" in several places and "FOX" on bottom of stock. This rifle had to have been acquired by the Studio before 1921 as after that date it became "20 Century Fox" This type of rifle can be seen in "Charge of the Light Brigade" among many other films. In .50-70 caliber. Originally made fron converted M1863 Springfield Rifles by the Government.  Butt plate is marked "7th Infantry E Company" in abreviation. This unit was at Fort Shaw during Red Clouds War in Montana Territory. It is the type used at the "Wagon Box Fight" and the "Hay Field Fight" along the Bozeman Trail. All complete and with the Studio Markings a real piece of Americana to be sure. Sold as is with no returns accepted. Can be picked up in Reno and is exempt from regulation due to it's age (antique). Shipping $35.00
